## Component copy in the system prompt

Baseline presets live in each primitive’s `defaultNode` and are summarized in `aiRef` (injected via `buildComponentStructureRef()`). **Do not** maintain a parallel “defaults” or “gotchas” list in `builder-knowledge.ts` for specific widgets — it duplicates design judgment the model already has and drifts from code.

Keep `builder-knowledge` focused on **how to use this product**: tools, schema, formulas, theme injection, and project rules. Component-specific behavior belongs in `aiRef` (and rarely one line in **Color rules** if it applies to all edits).

Any tool name referenced in builder knowledge or `aiRef` must exist in `lib/ai/builder-tools.ts`. (See "Class of Bug 1" in the audit section above.)

---

### Rule: Keep aiRef Strings in Sync With Registered Tools

Every `aiRef` string in `lib/builder/primitive-components.ts` that names a tool is a contract. When a tool is added, renamed, or removed in `lib/ai/builder-tools.ts`:

1. Search `primitive-components.ts` for the old tool name
2. Update every occurrence to the new name or replacement
3. Search `builder-knowledge.ts` for the old tool name and update there too

Failure to do this produces Class of Bug 1 (dead tool references) silently — there is no compile error.

